    "updated_at": "2015-07-07T22:02:44Z",
    "body": "@paulcbetts maybe we're mixing up terminology, can you help clarify?\n\nWindows has two native mechanisms for displaying notifications:\n1. [Notifications](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ee330740%28v=vs.85%29.aspx) (What you mention above as tray balloons. Supported in XP+)\n   ![win7notifications](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1829485/8558127/06a3580e-24b7-11e5-8213-991b9fdded2a.png)\n2. [Toast Notifications](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/hh465391.aspx), supported in Win8+. Only apps using the new app model (Modern) can use this.\n   ![win8toast](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1829485/8558218/957b3b8c-24b7-11e5-8c16-6718e26064b1.jpg)\n\nI'm assuming what you mean by notifications is Google's desktop notifications (e.g. Slack's notifications), correct?\n![googletoast](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1829485/8558248/c146c466-24b7-11e5-9ac5-f88e83ee75fe.png)\n\nWhen I hear notifications for Windows, I think of 1 & 2. I was a Program Manager on Windows for 9 years so that's what I think of :)\n\nIn what cases do you expose Balloons to developers in Electron?\n"
  },
