    "created_at": "2015-07-07T22:08:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-07T22:08:42Z",
    "body": "> In what cases do you expose Balloons to developers in Electron?\n\nThese are exposed on their own object called `Tray`, which lets you do everything'ish that Shell_NotifyIcon does\n\n> Toast Notifications, supported in Win8+.\n\nYeah, so this is what we should add to Electron, they actually can be used from Desktop apps as well (unofficially in Win8, and officially in Win10), via the same COM / WinRT'y API. The only caveat is that you must have a shortcut in the Start Menu or else they don't show in Win8. Outlook does this for example. \n\n> Google's desktop notifications\n\nChrome's desktop notifications are actually custom-implemented and aren't in Electron (they're part of Chrome's notification system with the Bell in the tray and Google Now and stuff). \n\n> (e.g. Slack's notifications)\n\nSlack's notifications are actually custom code that are _none_ of these options above! What a world!\n"
  },
